animal.description:
Hello everyone! My name is Myla - you might have seen me on the CMHS page a few times over the past year. What a long year it has been! I was brought to CMHS by my former guardian, who wanted to make sure that I found a great home that she unfortunately could no longer provide. From a young age, I was a little nervous around new people. As I grew up, this became what some might call 'stranger danger'. This basically means that I am really unsure when I meet a new person, so I need a very gradual introduction to help me get to know them. But once I know and trust a person, they are my best friend!! As they always say - quality over quantity - right?

In all seriousness though, this has been a big challenge for me. How am I supposed to find a home when I am not comfortable meeting new people?! Thankfully, I entered the Pawsitive Support Program at CMHS where I learned some really great training skills. I am a rock star a loose leash walking and targeting, if I do say so myself!

Please give me a chance today and I promise all our hard work will pay off together!

animal.description:
Monty V is the name and my game is naps and tail wags.  I'm a spry 10-year old Shiba Inu/Heeler mix who is easy going, loves my foster dog and cat siblings, goes potty outside and hangs out in my crate when needed.  When I was a young lad, I walked to doggie daycare uphill both ways.  These days, I prefer a shorter walk and a human best friend who will share my golden years with me.  My foster mom hasn't introduced me yet to children, but so far I've exceeded all of her expectations.  P.S. Will you be my Valentine?



My adoption fee is $75 and includes my spay/neuter, vaccinations, wellness exam, heartworm test, and microchip! If you're interested in meeting/adopting me, please visit www.rescueonespringfield.com/our-adoption-process/adoption-application/ and fill out the form! We do adopt out of state with vet references and video home check. *Adopter is responsible for coming to get the dog and returning the dog if the adoption does not work out* 

Don't forget to LIKE us on Facebook!-www.facebook.com/rescueonespringfield

*Remember, dogs are pack animals. Because of this, Rescue One does not adopt to outdoor-only homes. Pets are family and are not disposable.  Please make sure that you are 100% committed to a pet before considering adding one to your home.

animal.description:
Kiefer has so many great qualities that we couldn't even possibly name them all! He is a bundle of energy and very much a people dog. He'll love going on any dog-friendly errands with you, happily hopping in the car to go on a ride. He loves going on walks, no matter the weather! Cold or rain doesn't get this happy guy down. Kiefer loves to play and chase after a small tennis ball, and will happily go after it as many times as you're willing to throw it. After some good playtime, Kiefer becomes a little couch potato and loves to snuggle. He is a quick learner and picked up "sit" quickly. Overall, Kiefer is a total delight who will make a fabulous companion for some lucky home!

Please note we are working with limited staff/volunteers at this time. For full details of our current adoption appointment policy, please see https://savinggracenc.org/adoption-appointments-during-this-time/. Highlights:

We are working with a very limited staff/volunteer base

We do not have the people power to respond to emails/call about specific dogs

Our appointments are limited to 2 people at a time and for a maximum of 30 minutes.

Please arrive at your appointment ready to meet the dogs we have available. At this time, many dogs are in foster families or not yet posted on our website. Be flexible and ready to meet any number of wonderful dogs available onsite at the time of your appointment.

All puppies and dogs at Saving Grace are crate trained, have been spayed/neutered, are up to date on their vaccinations, are on heartworm preventative and have been microchipped. Their adoption fee is $375.00. Each has been carefully screened for disposition and temperament in order to provide your home with a safe companion that will enjoy life as your new family member.

Our Adoption Form can be completed online at our website at https://savinggracenc.org/how-to-adopt/ .

An Adoption Form is required before setting up an appointment to meet with a potential adoptee or a foster home.

Sending an Adoption Form does not commit you to an adoption, it simply provides us with background information on potential homes.

If you'd like to donate to help cover the cost of care for these wonderful dogs awaiting new homes, please visit the donate page on our website at https://savinggracenc.org/donate-now/ .

Saving Grace is a small, non-profit 501-C3 organization operated by volunteers only. Most of our animals come from rural animal control shelters where lack of space and resources limit their time and adoption possibilities. Thank you for choosing Saving Grace! We look forward to helping you find your new companion and family member.

ABOUT GOLIATH: Goliath is a sweet man with a very calm demeanor. He can take a little time to warm up to new people and would love a home that's willing to work with him on socialization. 

Goliath walks very nicely on a leash and is a huge cuddle bug! He will also take a treat gently and sit on command. Goliath might do best in a home with older children that respect and understand that he can be nervous sometimes. Goliath can't wait to find his forever home where he can fully come out of his shell and be a great companion.

animal.description:
Are you active, up for some adventure, but also love cuddling on the couch? Then Milo is your guy! Described by his foster as the best guy they have ever met, Milo is wise, gentle, and fun. Milo loves to run, explore the woods, chomp on snow, and cuddle with his toys. Milo is looking for a family that is active, loves being outdoors, will stimulate his mind (he is really smart!), and will treat him like a member of the family.

Age: 3 years old

Breed: Husky

Weight: 60 lbs

Kid-friendly: Milo can be a little jumpy, so we are recommending older, considerate children only.

Dogs: Yes! Milo is a very mellow dog. He will defer to the "alpha" dog in the house, but might get uncomfortable in environments like a dog park, because he is so passive.

Cats: Probably not. He has not had experience with cats in a home, but Milo has a very strong prey drive.

Crate trained: No. Milo has ALOT of anxiety being in a kennel. When created, Milo will try to escape the crate, often times injuring his nose. In his foster home, Milo is free to move around the house. He does better if doors are open so he has "access" to his people.

Potty trained: Yes!

Likes: Milo loves being outside, eating chicken and rice, running / walking, cuddling at home with his humans, toys, car rides, and marrow bones!

Health concerns: Milo has had some teeth pulled, and his teeth are not in the best shape. Milo will need regular brushing and dental cleanings.

Behaviors: Separation anxiety. Milo's foster family is working on leaving him alone for short periods of time. They are slowly increasing his time alone, but start to notice signs of SA after 10 minutes. Milo has been destructive when left alone. This is something Milo's adopting family will need to continue to work on, with lots of patience, love, and understanding.

Adoption fee: $425

Adopters will be responsible for continued preventatives, follow-up appointments, and medications (if applicable).

$50 discount for seniors (65+) and veterans. Adoption fees help pay for the dog's veterinary exam, vaccinations (rabies, distemper, and bordetella), HW test, blood panel, a microchip, and spay/neuter if needed and additional health needs specific to each animal.

animal.description:
This is what we do know about Mrs. Peabody.  She is in rescue because her owner passed away.  She is a Cocker Spaniel mix about 7-8 years old weighing about 18 pounds.  She is very shy and timid at first and she will not allow you to pick her up until she gets to know you better. Once she sees you as her person she is a very sweet little girl and will follow you every where.  She is good with dogs of all sizes (but is not looking for a playmate) and could care less about cats.  We have not seen her around children but because of her trust issues we feel a home without children is best.  She is house broken and rides good in the car.  She takes treats gently and has no food aggression issues.  

Unfortunately, we have some sad news to share.  ?
We received the results of Mrs. Peabody's blood work and she has been diagnosed with early stage kidney failure.  Because of this she is not a candidate for anesthesia, so she will not be able to have the surgery to remove the tumor from her backside or to have her dental cleaning/work that she needs.  The vet feels the tumor is not cancerous and it doesn't seem to bother her at all.  For now, the vet has prescribed her some special food to best support her kidneys and we will continue to make her days (however long that may or may not be) as comfortable and happy as possible. 

Mrs. Peabody will require regular grooming, which will be an added expense for any adopter, but be warned Mrs. Peabody does not tolerate her feet being touched and does not like being groomed. so she requires medication in order to be groomed, which will also be an added cost as well.  

She is adorable but she is not for every family and we will be choosey as to where she goes.  

If you are interested in adopting this sweet little so she can live out her days with her very own family, please fill out an application on our website at fairytails-rescue.weebly.com

Moxie is an energetic girl with a LOT of love to give! She was rescued from a life outdoors and now thoroughly enjoys her life in a home. She is a huge cuddle bug and will race over to curl up wherever you are, usually right on top of you! She's exceedingly smart and already knows how to sit, lay down, wait at doors and for her meals, and is working on giving her toys back so you can throw them again. She is trained to sleep in her crate, though we're still working through the housebreaking process. Moxie lives with a cat and has been well behaved around him.
Moxie's new home must be one with a physically fenced yard. Electronic/invisible fences will not be considered. No exceptions.
Her new home must also be one that is willing to commit to two rounds of training classes with an approved trainer or training facility.
If you think that Moxie would be a great fit for your family, please head to www.homefurever.com to fill out an application.

While not all are in the immediate area, once we have processed and approved your application, we will move the dog to our adoptive area for you to meet, greet and hopefully adopt. That does not mean it automatically goes to another family but you should be aware of the fact that until you are approved and set up for the meet/greet.. the dog could get adopted by another applicant.This older lady is easy, sweet and loving. She has had a lifetime of learning how to be a good dog, even though for a long time she was not valued or cared for with love. Her foster says she is outstanding and fit right into her home, as she will to yours, like she had been there all her life. Friendly, happy, outgoing and accepting of whatever comes her way, Cassie could easily be one of the best dogs you have ever had. Because most of our dogs were picked up as strays, we have no knowledge of any behavior or health issues.  Stray dogs are held for 72 hours so that the owners have a chance to redeem them. animal.description:
Yugo is a hidden gem. Such a sweet boy. He is only 1 and has been extremely traumatized. He is looking for a
home that can be very patient with him as he needs time to open up and trust people. He is still pretty confused and nervous in general with all the changes happening in his life, but is starting to pick up on daily routines, learning to go to the bathroom outside etc. He is totally peaceful with  the other dog and cat in his foster home. Sudden moves and being touched still startles him, but he has started to solicit pets a little bit and follows his foster parents around. 
*
 I see a 75 lb dog who is even afraid of a little cat and i cant help but wonder what the hell his life was like prior to being dumped, but at the end of the day where he came from doesn’t matter. What matters now is where he is going. We are so SO thankful to his fosters for taking a chance with him, being so patient and loving and sending consistent updates on his progress. If you are interested in meeting Yugo, please know that it will be a slow road with him, but he is the sweetest most loving pup once he opens up. He is great with other dogs once he is comfortable and has zero aggression towards cats.

He has not been neutered yet, but the vet will take care of that soon. He is up-to-date on vaccinations and will be heartworm tested an microchipped upon adoption. Come meet him in Run 811 using ID#627042.

Please note, all of the pet listings on Friends of Shelter Animals for Cobb are done by volunteers, not shelter staff. If this pet came in as lost (not an owner surrender), we don't know how they might be with children, other pets, or if house trained. You can bring your pet to the shelter for a meet & greet with your potential new best friend. When calling the shelter about a cat or dog, please use THE ID NUMBER, names are oftentimes made up by volunteers. 

This pet and many others are available for adoption from the Cobb County Animal Shelter 1060 Al Bishop Dr. Marietta, GA 30008, call (770) 499-4136 for more information. Shelter hours are: Tues. - Sun. 10:30 a.m. to 4:30 p.m. by appointment only until further notice, CLOSED Mondays & Holidays.

animal.description: It seems like the bigger they are, the gentler they are. And that is true of "gentle giant" Rupert. Still, at almost ninety pounds, he can be quite strong on a leash, so he has been fitted for a harness. He loves to be with people and can be affectionate and loving. He also has fun with toys, (the big strong kind!). Rupert had to overcome neuter surgery, dewclaw removal, and a URI when he first came to the League but now he is raring to go! We are still learning about Rupert but if a big, and we mean BIG dog, is on your wish list, plan to visit with Rupert. He is just two years old and will need a family who will spend a good deal of time exercising and guiding him so that his size and energy does not become overbearing. To meet Rupert, call 513-735-2299 to schedule an appointment.

animal.description: Hello, my name is Polly and I'm a lovely five year old Black Mouth Cur/Pit Bull Terrier mix. I was originally found as a stray in Arkansas so we don't know anything about my history, how sad is that for a sweet little girl of my years?. Fortunately for me, I was eventually picked up, and then I made the long trip from Arkansas to Michigan! It's a good thing that I have an easy going personality and I'm actually looking forward to a new start with my life. Recently, I partook of a temperament test and although I didn't graduate at the top of my class, I wasn't at the bottom either. I passed my food and yummy treat test, my kissy-huggy test and my toy sharing test. I didn't rate so high on my dog interaction; especially with another female, so I would need to meet any new doggy companions before I move in. And as for cats; I wasn't able to introduce myself with any at this time. Also, it's been advised that I live with older children because I tend to jump up when I'm happy! I hope you can come meet me in person so I can share some of my loving with you. Please fill out an application and make an appointment today.
animal.name: Polly

animal.description:
Meet Missie! She is a sweet 5 year old, 50 lb hound who likes to follow her nose, but is great on the leash and is 99% housetrained. Missie is great with other dogs, loves cuddles and toys and most of all, food! She plays with the other dogs at her foster home, and will need a fenced yard to keep her scenting ability from leading her astray. Her foster mom reports that she is even a bit mischievous, stealing shoes and gloves when she is not looking! Missie is a bit thin right now, but will fill out in no time, and is ready to find her forever home. 
She is spayed and up to date on vaccines and preventatives.

The adoption fee for this dog is $350 which includes routine vetting and spay/neuter. 

For more information, please contact France at fbognon@petconnectrescue.org

**If you're viewing this on Petfinder, please visit www.petconnectrescue.org to complete our non-binding application.**

Meet  Gorgeous Georgie!  OMG HE IS THE PERFECT PET!  ONE OF OUR BEST FOSTER DOGGIES EVER! 

SUPER friendly, a happy, little guy (8 LBS) who meets everybody with a wagging tail. Georgie just turned 12, but acts younger, with pep in his step. He has a grade 4 heart murmur, but is on NO meds and is extremely energetic!  Georgie enjoys his walks and does very well on his leash. He is looking for a forever home {with at least one available lap at all times }and will be a great companion to his new owner. Georgie is house trained, sleeps through the night in his crate, knows basic commands, rides well in the car and so much more! He has an easy-going personality and a wonderful temperament.  He goes with the flow just enjoys being with people.  

This darling dude deserves only the best...an at home family who has Maltese experience and unlimited love to shower on him....it will be returned tenfold!
For more information and application for adoption please email 
petrealtors@yahoo.com  Adoption fee $250

animal.description:
Teddy, is a 7 month old lab mix and is almost 50 lbs.  He's an absolute sweetie but is very timid and skittish.  The 1st time he meets someone he barks at them but you can see his whole body shaking.  Once he gets to know the person, he won't stop loving you.  He's his foster moms little shadow.

Good with other dogs and wants to play.  Same with cats but can't figure out why they don't want to play.  Teddy likes kids but he's got energy and is a jumper so really small kids would need to be supervised around him.

Teddy loves to go for walks. We've been going for 2 walks a day.  And he's learned very quickly how to walk nicely on a leash.  While he's got energy, he also enjoys laying at your feet in the evening.  Teddy really likes chew toys. A big chewer, we've gone through a number of toys but he never chews on anything but  chew toy.

Teddy does great in his kennel.  Overnight he prefers being able to see you so we have his kennel in our bedroom and he does great.  He's had a few accidents but has been learning fast to go outside.

Teddy is a wonderful snuggler and loves to give kisses.

If you would like to be considered as a potential adopter for one of our great dogs, please go to our website- www.luckymuttsrescue.org and submit an application. Our application process includes landlord approval and vet checks. Please make sure all of your information is current and accurate, including a valid email address and phone numbers. Inaccuracies and/or incomplete data will delay and/or cancel your application.  We strive to process all applications in a timely manner, but with the high volume of applications we are receiving, it is taking anywhere from 1-3 weeks. animal.description:
Hi! My name is Mocha and I am a 7-month-old retriever mix that weighs 41lbs. One of my favorite things to do is give kisses! I just love to get my energy out and play with the resident kids (ages 6 and 8).  They run around with me and throw the ball for me. I even like to get in on their dance parties.  I also really like to play with the resident dog. We play tug and wrestle.  The other elderly resident dog likes to be left alone so I do not bother him.  I know my foster mom likes to complain about all of the snow but I just LOVE it! I like to run in it, stick my face in it, and roll around in it. I know when we go outside it is time to go potty.  I have had a few accidents but I am doing better every day. Some things that scare me are when we go for car rides. I am also a little unsure of people I do not know.  I will bark at them to tell them to stay away but if they give me a treat, I will take it from them.  I don't always like to go into my kennel but after a few minutes, I am okay and lay down. I am young and still learning and if you want a snuggly sweet dog, I am your girl!

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.UPDATE: Bruce got adopted and then was returned back to PRBJ. His owner was putting his snap on collar back on him and at that moment Bruce got out of her grasp and went after her dog and bit his ear and her adult daughter got nipped while trying to break them up. We feel maybe his hair got stuck in the clip and spooked him. The owner stated that the night before Bruce and her dog were fine together, no problems they played with no incident, Bruce was wonderful. Bruce has never shown any aggression at the rescue with staff or other dogs. Bruce is a 4 year old neutered male. He friendly with cats and dogs. He is a sweet cuddle bug. He absolutely loves the outdoors and loves nature trails. He can run forever if you let him. When he is indoors he is a couch potato. He is potty trained, crate trained (command word is 'house:). He will pull you when he sees squirrels/lizards when on a leash. He loves to give you kisses. He has been around kids 2 and up and has done amazing around them. Bruce even went to an event where there was tons of people of all ages with loud music playing and did amazing at the event. He listens to positive praise and he does aim to please. He is a very loving dog who just needs a great home with someone who can give him the attention he deserves. Please let's help this sweet dog get the forever home he has been waiting for.
His owner had to give him up because he moved back home and parent did not want the dog in home.

animal.description:
To be considered for adopting a dog from Canine Lifeline, you must have an approved application must be on file. Please visit http://www.caninelifeline.org/adoption-process/ for more information about our adoption process and to submit an online application.

Echo is a gorgeous 2 year-old Aussie mix with a bobtail who came to us from a rural county dog shelter after having been shot multiple times both in the face and torso. This sweet dog has no doubt had an awful time of it recently at the hands of a horrible person or people but he is now on the mend and ready to make a fresh start in a brand new home. All things considered, Echo was very lucky that the gunshot damage wasn't more serious. The bullet fragments that hit him in the face fractured some teeth that had to be removed while those that entered his shoulder and hip areas didn't hit any vital organs fortunately. Those wounds are now healing nicely. Echo still has some bullet fragments in his body but those are best left alone as it can produce more harm than good to try to remove them. Although he's understandably still a little ouchy, Echo is a very happy, friendly dog who gets along well with other dogs and has done well meeting new people too. He would do best in a mature home without young kids and would enjoy having a canine buddy. Echo would also enjoy having a yard with an aboveground fence to allow him to play safely. He has done well with his crate training in his foster home so should be able to master the house rules without too much trouble in his new home. He will eagerly sit for a treat and may know other commands that we haven't discovered yet. Echo enjoys going for a walk and would make an excellent trail buddy for an active person once his wounds are completely healed. We can't wait to see this wonderful dog living his best life with his new person or family. There are no cats in Echo's foster home so we don't know how he would be living with them. Echo weighs about 40 pounds and his adoption fee is $350. He's neutered, heartworm negative and on monthly preventative, up to date on vaccinations including bivalent canine influenza, wormed, on flea and tick preventative, and microchipped. As part of the adoption process, all adopters must commit to a two-week adjustment period to make sure it's a great match before the adoption is finalized. Please email info@caninelifeline.org if you're interested in Echo. An approved application is required before we schedule meets with any of our dogs. Please note that we don't place our dogs in homes with children under 7 years of age. We correspond via email so please check your junkmail or spam folder to make sure our reply hasn't landed in there. Please visit our website at www.caninelifeline.org to see more photos of Echo and to submit an online application if you live in Northeast OH.

animal.description:
Schnauzer alert! Tyler was on the lam in Beloit, Kansas, for a very long time. With the invaluable help from some kind people he was finally caught and brought to The Sanctuary for some good food, a warm, soft place to sleep, and help learning that humans can be trusted. 

As you can see, Tyler has made some dog friends. In fact, he still prefers dog to humans and will need a canine friend in his new home. He is making progress on leash and trust in general with humans. He has so much potential. 

Call or text The Pet Connection at 913-671-7387 if you'd like to learn more about Tyler.

INTERESTED IN ADOPTING THIS PET? Fill out an Adoption Application now! Appointments can also be made to meet a pet by calling us at 913-671-PETS (913-671-7387).  

ADOPTION INFORMATION:
Prior to adoption, our animals are: 
**Tested for diseases 
**Vaccinated 
**Spayed/neutered 
**Microchipped 

NO COST adoptions with an encouraged donation are accepted. 

The Pet Connection also offers adopters a FREE veterinary examination and a medical care support plan for 60 days after adoption, as well as lifetime behavioral training, safe sanctuary for pets returned in emergency situations, extensive assistance with lost and found pets, and other expert pet services in a variety of areas, including pet selection, behavioral issues, general training, nutrition, and transition to adoptive homes.

Please visit our website at www.thepetconnection.org for more information about The Pet Connection and for a full listing of our available pets, 

Call or text The Pet Connection at 913-671-7387 if you can foster, adopt, or sponsor a special needs dog or cat! 

The Pet Connection is a membership organization operating a no-kill adoption center in Shawnee, Kansas.

animal.description:
Hi my name is Milan and I am female terrier mix found with Vienna running around and neither of us was reported missing so here we are looking for homes. I am only about 9 months old and I weigh 16lbs. I am a typical puppy full of energy and wanting to play and wrestle all the time. I am athletic and can jump and negotiate lots of obstacles, so I will need a secure yard and/or someone who will want to walk and play with me and use up some of my puppy energy! I love to paly and interact with other dogs so a playmate sibling would be a great benefit to me. I am crate trained, but to be honest, I am not a fan and will entertain myself by rearranging everything in the crate and tearing it up !! yes, I am all puppy and will need guidance, training, patience and lots of love to become the best dog ever and your best pal.  If you would like to adopt me, please put in an application on the rescue's website www.floprva.org that is the ONLY way to adopt from this rescue. You can also donate there to help keep this rescue open as they may have to close, which would be so sad for dogs like me in need of rescue and a helping hand. 
Love, 
Milan xo

animal.description: You're heard someone say Good Golly Miss Molli!!     Where here she is.    This 2 yr old girl can be quite full of herself.    She definitely needs a fenced in yard to work off her energy and will be fine if there is a male for her to play with but Molli can be rough at times.    Just needs someone to oversee the play time and let her know what is or isn't allowed.   Crating is out of the question for this girl.   She definitely does not like one.     Looking for someone who will be patient and take the time to get her thru a few obstacles.    She can be anxious in the car but over time that can be corrected.    Also, she can be leash reactive but with training, that too can be work with.   We don't know how she is with cats, so it be best that there aren't any.    As for children, no young ones.   Teenagers would be fine.   This girl is sweet as can be and once she adjusts into her new home, will be the love bug you expect her to be.   If interested, go to www.dvdpa.org and then to adopt to fill out the on-line application.

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.
Name: Eldora
DOB: 10/18/20
Weight: 15lb
Adoption Fee: $450

*NEEDS A PHYSICAL FENCE*
Eldora aka Ellie is a spunky girl that is slowly learning how to puppy! You see, Eldora did not have it easy when she was born. She was found on the Pine Ridge Reservation with seven other puppies - all of them struggling to find food, water and warmth. Despite it all, she is so sweet and a joy to foster! Eldora is being fostered with Breckenridge, Revelstoke and Lutsen.

Because of this, Eldora does require a special adopter! She needs a family that can be patient as she slowly comes out of her shell, one that can teach her manners and properly socialize her with other animals and people and one that is committed to handling an energetic, big puppy!

Eldora does require a yard with a fence. Everything is brand new to her and she can be easily scared. She will also require a harness and leash attached to her at all times until she is comfortable in her new home - inside and even outside in the fenced yard.

Eldora would also do best in a home with no kids or older kids only. The toddler in her foster home scares her with all of his toddler noises but she does do will with the foster's older (10yr+) children. Eldora is mouthy! She was never taught that bones are for chewing - not people! Most kids will not like this - and something her forever family will need to work on.

In the meantime if you have questions or are interested in me, please fill out an adoption application at www.ruffstartrescue.org.

An adoption application is the best way to show your interest in an animal.

Please check out our website, www.ruffstartrescue.org for more details and additional pictures on any of our animals!

All Ruff Start dogs and cats are spayed/neutered, up to date on age appropriate vaccines, microchipped, dewormed, and on monthly flea/tick and heartworm prevention (dogs) as well as heartworm tested (dogs).

Ruff Start Rescue is a foster based rescue. Animals are located in homes throughout Minnesota. We do not have a facility where animals are kept.

Ruff Start Rescue Adoption Policies: http://www.ruffstartrescue.org/info/display?PageID=11744

animal.description:
Hi there. I'm Dietrich... Deets for short. I am a feisty but loving lady looking for my forever family. I love adventures with my brothers and sisters, playing with toys, cuddling, and long walks on the beach. Could you be my new mama or daddy?

I am good with other dogs.

I haven't been around cats or kids.

I will need a family that understands that I am a puppy and will need training.

I sleep in my crate at night.

I love all toys and treats.

My favorite thing to do is run around.

I'm working on going potty training but I'm not quite there yet.

I'm super friendly.

I would love to have another dog in the house but it's not required.

I would also love a fenced in yard but again, not required.

I have had my first and second rounds of puppy shots.

I am microchipped and spayed.

My mama was a German Shepard and my dad was probably a lab so I'm going to be a big girl.

If interested, please
complete the
Adoption Application
on our website at
www.NeedyPaws.org
and we will contact you.
Adopters must live within an hour's drive of St. Louis, MO.

Our $250 adoption fee includes up-to-date vaccinations, heartworm testing and preventative, spay/neuter and microchip.

We are a 100% foster-based rescue and all of our dogs live in approved foster homes. We are dedicated to finding the best Forever Homes, and will perform home visits and conduct veterinarian and reference checks for each potential adopter.

Meet Brody!

This gorgeous boy loves to go for walks, and he's good on a leash.
He is a young, active and friendly!  And when the day is done, you can count on lots of snuggles from this sweet guy. He has a beautiful, shiny silver/grey coat, with markings of reddish gold. And that face - oh so handsome!

Sweet Brody was on Death Row in a high kill facility in Georgia, and we were able to rescue him in the nick of time.

Brody is 1 year old, weighs 48 lbs, has all of his required vaccines, and is neutered and microchipped.

Did we mention he has the SWEETEST temperament??? He loves other dogs, and he's happy to spend time with humans of all ages.  Because of his activity level, we believe he'd do best in a home with older children or no children.

If you are interested in adopting this delightful young boy, please complete an adoption application at https://www.heartsandtails.org/adoption-application/.

PLEASE NOTE that due to the overwhelming number of inquiries we receive daily, we can only respond to those who have completed an online application, and appear to be a good match. animal.description:
This is Athena. She is a female German Shepard mix about 18 mos to 2 yrs. She is currently in foster care in Olympia, Washington. Looking for her forever home. Please apply if interested. Thank you!

This is a posting for L & S Dog Diggity Rescue. You can fill out and application below. Yes you must COPY and PASTE this application link.

https://shaynesrescue.com/adoption-application-ls-dog-diggity/

All adopted pups and dogs are transported by our transport unit to WA/OR families when fully vetted, spayed/neutered and microchipped. For information on how to adopt me, please contact my foster parents at info@dogdiggityrescue.com. L&S Dog Diggity Rescue is headquartered in San Antonio, Texas, where there are over 350,000 homeless pets. We save homeless and abandoned dogs and find them loving forever homes in other areas, where pet homelessness is not epidemic. All of our pets are located here, in San Antonio, and we partner with rescues to provide transportation for our pets to their new homes. Our adoption fee includes vet care (vaccinations, spay/neuter, microchipping, etc), as well as transportation and health certificate. Please contact us to ask about our adoption process and our adoption fees. You can contact us directly at info@dogdiggityrescue.com, or fill out an application at https://shaynesrescue.com/adoption-application-ls-dog-diggity/

Important: If you are interested in this pup/dog, please fill out the application (link listed above). The rescue will contact you once the application is received. Although we strive to answer everyone, due to the high volume of inquiries we receive, we cannot guarantee a response to all emails. Filling out the application is the ONLY way and ensures a response from the rescue. In addition, while you are emailing us, if others apply, you lose out adopting the dog you chose. We have hundreds and hundreds of puppies/dogs available so there really is no need to apply anywhere else. However, if you are applying or have applied anywhere else, we do need to know that.

SHANYE'S FOSTERS is a group of foster parents in the Olympia/Tumwater area. We foster dogs for rescues and assist them in adopting/rehoming of their pups/dogs by listing on this site. Many dogs posted here are available to pre adopt NOW directly from the rescue. The only ones in foster in the NW specifically state that. We have very few fosters so most need to be pre adopted. All adoption fees go towards rescuing more dogs in need. No one receives a salary. Shayne's Fosters is not responsible for any experience you have with any dog you might see posted on this site. They are the property of the sponsoring rescue who will supply all medical supporting records which is given with each dog when adopted.

Our adoption fees cover all medical costs to make sure the pups are appropriately vaccinated, microchipped, dewormed, and spayed/ neutered. It also covers the cost of transportation from Texas and the necessary health certificate documentation. The fees also include a negative heart-worm test for any dogs over 6 months. Some dogs/pups have additional medical, including but not limited to FHO, ACL, hernias, dental, and a myriad of other vetting. If the adoption fees seem high (which never cover the true cost of rescue), we recommend fostering for a good rescue. Fostering ensures you incur no vet bills and no boarding fees. We are always in need of good fosters. We are all volunteers who donate our time and resources to help save as many dogs/pups as we possibly can.

Thank you for choosing to adopt a rescue pup/dog. Worldwide over 1/2 or 1 billion puppies/dogs are PTS yearly. thousands and thousand daily (yes entire litters, pregnant/nursing moms are PTS daily just in U.S. shelters. Yes even entire litters of puppies yes DAILY in many US shelters! We firmly believe there is NO breed other than rescue for all species. Thank you for being part of the village it takes to save these precious lives.

animal.description:
Rihanna is a gorgeous black, spayed female shar pei. She is about 8 years old and loves everyone (people and dogs). She is super affectionate and was living with other dogs and is in a foster home with another female pei.

Rihanna rides well in a car, knows how to use a dog door and is potty trained, isn't a fan of crates, and does fine with both baths and nail clipping....easy all the way around. She loves to lounge around with you, but is also great on walks. She does appear to have some selective hearing...could be a shar lei thing or could be hearing loss due to age. and did we mention she loves treats and food?

If you are looking for a sweet, well mannered, well taken care of pei, Rihanna is your dream girl. She is up to date on vaccines, is microchipping and is currently waiting for her forever home. She is currently fostering in the Los Angeles area.

Litter of 7 puppies 6 girls and 1 boy. They came from a rural shelter where they had been abandoned. Please watch our facebook page ( facebook.com/luvnpupz ) for locations and which pups will be there. PLEASE NOTE: This pet has been posted by Friends of Campbell County Animal Control, Rustburg, VA. For questions about the pet, please email us at FOACinfo@gmail.com. All adoptions begin with an application, found under the "Animals" tab on our website, friendsofcampbellcounty.org. *Unaltered babies under the age of six months can be adopted only to residents of Campbell County, the City of Lynchburg, and counties touching Campbell County. *Unaltered adult pets six months or older will need to be sterilized before they can be adopted outside our local area of Campbell County, the City of Lynchburg, or counties touching Campbell. *We do not promote dog adoptions to homes where an invisible fence is the fencing of choice. *We do not permit cats or kittens to be declawed following adoption.

animal.description:
Honey Bee recently gave birth to triplet boys and is available for pre-adoption! Her spay is scheduled for February 17th and her puppies will need to be completely weaned before she can go to her new home.

Honey Bee is potty trained and has lots of energy, but calms down once she gets enough exercise. She will need an active home  with another pup and a backyard to burn off her energy. She loves to sunbathe and is an overall happy girl!

Honey Bee will do best in a home with older children and does great with other dogs and cats!

animal.description:
Meet LuLu!  

This little chi/pom mix has a grumpy-looking face but is actually a sweetie!  She has a soft plush thick coat and is about 10lbs, and previously spayed.  

She was surrendered to the local pound when her owner passed and the relative caring for her had to move... she was said to be 5 years old but looks more like at least twice that and is definitely an older lady.  She’s been ok with calm dogs but really craves human attention.  We are still getting to know her and she will get a medical work up and much needed dental very soon but email njwoof@cs.com 
if you think you would be interested in meeting her once she’s ready... 

Due to COVID-19, we will not be holding our Sunday adoption events until further notice, but we can schedule socially distant appointments with a specific dog outdoors at our vet’s office:
VCA Morris Plains Animal Hospital 
3009 Rt 10 East 
Morris Plains (Denville on GPS) NJ 07950
Now is the perfect time to open your home to a needy dog!  Submit an application from our website www.secondchance.petfinder.com to speed up the adoption process
All our dogs reside in foster care in Northern NJ until adoption. We are a small all-volunteer organization focused on rescuing local dogs from area shelters, as well as accepting some surrenders and puppy mill rescues.

animal.description:
Is Penelope still available?? 

(Unfortunately, we will not reply to emails asking this question as we do not have the time or volunteers to do so. We update our website daily just so you will know the status right away).  PLEASE GO TO OUR WEBSITE for up to date information to find out.  Check the Gallery by putting your mouse on the photo. 
IF it says Pending, we chose someone, but they haven't met up yet.  If it says Adopted, then the dog has been happily united with a forever family.

IF nothing is there other than their name, they are still available.

APPLY if interested so you can be considered.

*Our page is updated daily. Please go to www.wowdogrescue.org for any updates.

Penelope is approx. 4 lb.  Most likely a Jack Russel/Chi/ and Maltese mix puppy.
(Basing this on what the other pups look like).  She was found in a box in an alley with 3 other puppies.  The lady that found them went door to door asking if they knew who these pups belonged too...but no one seemed to know. One neighbor wanted 1 of them and the 3 came to our rescue.  They are now 13 weeks old and are being vetted and spay/neutered.  Penelope is scheduled for Feb 16th to be spay.

Penelope has been with the foster for a few weeks with out any play mates, but she was great with her siblings when they were all together.  She is good with kids as she likes to play.

1st intro to people is she is shy, but then super sweet. She is getting used to loud noises but she is getting braver each time. Penelope likes to be in her crate at night because she feels safe there.   She will let her foster parents know when she has to go potty by going to the door.  She has only had 2 potty accidents in the home, so shes doing great with that! She is learning to walk on a leash.  She loves snuggling and falling asleep  on any one that will hold her.  She loves playing tug all day with her foster mom.  She rides well in the car, and normally falls to to sleep right away.  She has a kong toy that she loves filled with peanut butter, and it keeps her busy. Penelope's Foster says shes a very good listener
and learns quickly with treats.  She is very energetic, cheerful and sweet and the foster says she would make the new family proud if they rescued her!

Penelope will be spay, puppy shot series, Bordetella and Microchipped by 2/16/21  Penelope's adoption fee is set at $275.00

WE ARE NOT PETFINDER.  WE ARE NOT ADOPTAPET OR RESCUEME.

 We are W.O.W DOG RESCUE  Our application is on our website:

 www.wowdogrescue.org 

**PLEASE do not call or email to see if she is "still" available.  Her Gallery photo on our website will be updated daily and will state her status.  IF we have chosen someone, she will be marked "Pending".  IF she has been adopted, she will be marked "Adopted".

***Tired of not finding, or not being chosen for the dog of your dream?? 
 Consider Fostering with us...Our Fosters have 1st chance at adopting the dog they foster, while we pay for everything.  Its a win win for both! YOU get to see if this is a good match for your family, while the dog is being loved in your home...

animal.description:
If you are interested in adopting this dog, please fill out our dog adoption questionnaire and e-mail it to adoptioncenter@homewardtrails.org

Due to COVID-19 precautions, all animals for adoption through Homeward Trails can be met by appointment only. You can make an appointment to meet available dogs at our ADOPTION CENTER by going to https://www.signupgenius.com/go/20f084ea8ae2da5f49-meet and available cats at MEOW PALACE by going to https://www.signupgenius.com/go/20f084ea8ae2da5f49-meet1. 
For animals in FOSTER homes, please submit an online application and an adoption team will reply with next steps. We thank you for your patience as we work to keep saving lives during this difficult time. 

PLEASE VISIT THIS WEBSITE TO FIND THE ADOPTION QUESTIONNAIRE: http://www.homewardtrails.org/adopt-a-pet/adoption-forms/

Peanut just arrive from Puerto Rico! She is good with people and other dogs. Can you give her a forever home?

Adoption Coordinator: Homeward Trails Adoption Center
Location: Adoption Center
The adoption fee for this dog is $475. This fee DOES INCLUDE spay/neuter and microchip. 

We are proud to partner with the following veterinarians who offer a free first exam for your animal, exclusively for HT adopters: Caring Hands Animal Hospital, Palisades Veterinary Clinic, Sunshine Animal Hospital and Clarendon Animal Care and all VCA Animal Hospitals.

Additionally, any VCA hospital will cover illnesses up to $250 at no cost to any Homeward Trails adopter.

We also provide free online workshop with a professional dog trainer at Fur-Get Me Not within the first 30 days of adopting - just for HT adopters in the Arlington/Alexandria/Falls Church/DC area. Start your new dog out on the right foot with this valuable, expert guidance FREE!

You can save animals like this one by becoming a foster! Fosters are like way stations between high kill shelters and forever homes. We need fosters so that we can save dogs before they are euthanized at the shelters. If you are interested in becoming a foster, please check out our information about fostering by visiting http://www.homewardtrails.org/foster-a-pet/dog-and-cat-foster-program
